text: Roger Cook (born 20 August 1965) is a Western Australian politician who will become the next Premier of Western Australia and leader of the Western Australian Labor Party, following the resignation of Mark McGowan. He previously served as Deputy Premier. He has served as the member for Kwinana since 2008.
